The join filter returns a string which is the concatenation of the items of a sequence: <br>

{{ [1, 2, 3]|join }} <br>
{# returns 123 #}
The separator between elements is an empty string per default, but you can define it with the optional first parameter: <br>

{{ [1, 2, 3]|join('|') }} <br>
{# outputs 1|2|3 #}
A second parameter can also be provided that will be the separator used between the last two items of the sequence: <br>

{{ [1, 2, 3]|join(', ', ' and ') }}
{# outputs 1, 2 and 3 #}
